race.comment: LEAFICE (6) resumed here and looked a run short. Showed enough in her initial preparation to say this is winnable with the extra fitness. Chris Parnham is reunited and that's a positive lead. UNFORTUNATE LAD (2) just missed at Albany third-up showing more like his best. No surprise if he went on with it now. ACQUIRED TASTE (8) debuts and owns a Lark Hill trial win. CJP stays aboard and she maps for a soft run. Looks ready to race well.  Ditto BUSTER'S BABE (9) who won a recent Lark Hill trial for the Williams yard. Has the rail and is likely to race boldly for the new stable. TEMPUS TYCOON (5) has switched from a Victorian stable on a 307-day return. It's an ask, but her two starts have been in provincial Maidens, and she's looked forward placing in her two trials. The betting will be key.
